collections.name: Compound Mulisig signers are distinct humans!
Expansion Explained
collections.description:
Expansion Explained is a collection of 120 plotter paintings. The concept of expansion has been an essential element across many of Licia's generative works, such as Running Moon (2022, Art Blocks Curated) and Sparkling Goodbye (2023, Bright Moments). In 2024, Licia introduced her expansion algorithm to a broader audience through Painting With Plotters, a participatory design event hosted by the Victoria and Albert Museum. 

Expansion Explained is a continuation and a summary of the expansion algorithm presented during the Painting With Plotters event. Using her original Python-based algorithm, Licia produced a sequence of 120 images that illustrate the construction of the algorithm. Each image in the sequence was translated into a plotter-operating script and physically rendered with brush and fountain pen ink using a high-precision pen plotter (Axidraw V3/A3). The collection of 120 paintings is hosted on a custom-designed and 3D-printed display stand. The collection can be enjoyed individually as paintings, digitally as a stop-motion animation, and collectively as an assembled sculpture. 

This project is part of the digital section of Cure³ at Bonhams, curated by Alex Estorick and Foteini Valeonti of reGEN.

collections.description:
GrandpaDiaries – A Humorous Glimpse into the Daily Lives of Japanese Seniors
"GrandpaDiaries" is a hand-drawn illustration collection by an 80-year-old Japanese artist. This series captures the charm, humor, and wisdom that come with age, showcasing the delightful everyday moments of Japanese seniors. From sipping tea leisurely on the porch to searching for misplaced glasses or enjoying heartwarming interactions with grandchildren, each piece evokes a sense of nostalgia and warmth.

collections.name: Primal LUX SUPREME COLLECTION
collections.description:
The Primal LUX™ NFT Collection will seamlessly integrate the luxury and exclusivity of high-end ornamental reptile car wraps with the digital NFT space. Inspired by South Indian Naga lore, this NFT collection will focus on blending mythical elegance with cutting-edge blockchain technology. Each NFT will serve as a dynamic certificate of authenticity and unlock real-world benefits tied to Primal LUX™'s hypercars and luxury SUV wraps.

Unique Features of the Collection:

1. Digital Twin Utility

Each NFT corresponds to a specific swatch or design from the Primal LUX™ catalog (e.g., Ancient Guardian™ or Serpent Sovereign™ series).

NFT holders can redeem their digital twin for exclusive car wrap rolls, ensuring the NFT holds tangible real-world value.

2. Exclusivity and Scarcity

Limited edition NFTs align with the rarity of the physical swatches. For example:

Ancient Guardian™ Series: Only 3–5 NFTs per design.

Naga Royalty™ Series: Ultra-rare NFTs with bespoke 1:1 customization option
